12:41.270 --> 12:42.237
AND DO SOMETHING ELSE.

12:42.380 --> 12:43.711
THAT SEEMS
TO BE MY ROLE HERE.

12:43.860 --> 12:45.031
SO I'M JUST
GONNA SIT IN MY OFFICE

12:45.170 --> 12:48.139
AND SEE
WHAT HAPPENS NEXT, OKAY?

12:49.380 --> 12:51.177
- OH, MY GOD,
OH, MY GOD!

12:51.320 --> 12:54.289
MOTH ER-FREAKING-
DAM N-HELL-CRAP-BASTARD!

12:54.420 --> 12:55.523
I HATE HIM.

12:55.670 --> 12:57.001
I HATE MY HUSBAND,
I HATE HIM SO MUCH!

12:57.150 --> 12:59.209
HOW CAN THAT SON OF A BITCH
BE ON TRIAL RIGHT NOW?

12:59.360 --> 13:01.180
HE'S NEVER ON TRIAL,
AND I'M WITH CHILD!

13:01.330 --> 13:03.013
- BREATHE, GRACE.
- OH, YEAH.

13:03.160 --> 13:04.491
- OH,
YOU'RE DOING AMAZING.

13:04.640 --> 13:07.291
- [whimpers]
OH, GOD, I'M NOT PREPARED.

13:07.440 --> 13:09.226
I DIDN'T PACK
A CAR SEAT FOR THE BABY.

13:09.370 --> 13:11.122
HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO TAKE THE BABY HOME?

13:11.270 --> 13:13.090
- IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.
WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT, OKAY?

13:13.240 --> 13:14.468
- YOUR CONTRACTIONS
LOOK GREAT, GRACE.

13:14.620 --> 13:15.814
I THINK IT'S TIME TO PUSH.

13:15.960 --> 13:17.712
- UM, I'LL TAKE
THAT EPIDURAL NOW.

13:17.860 --> 13:19.919
- TOO LATE.
- WHAT?

13:20.070 --> 13:21.753
- TOO LATE.

13:21.900 --> 13:23.891
- OKAY, GRACE,
DON'T WORRY.

13:24.040 --> 13:25.553
YOU'RE GOING THROUGH HELL,

13:25.700 --> 13:27.930
AND THEN YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
A BEAUTIFUL, AMAZING BABY.

13:28.080 --> 13:29.172
- I THINK YOU'RE
THE MOST WONDERFUL PERSON

13:29.320 --> 13:31.356
I'VE EVER MET IN MY LIFE.

13:31.500 --> 13:32.944
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE SUCH A BITCH.

13:33.080 --> 13:34.638
- I THOUGHT
YOU WERE A BITCH.

13:34.770 --> 13:36.351
- I WANT A BIG PUSH.
ON ONE...

13:36.500 --> 13:38.229
TWO...
THREE.

13:38.360 --> 13:45.983
- [screaming]
I NEED DRUGS!

13:51.690 --> 13:53.920
- I BROUGHT YOU
SOME MILK AND COOKIES.

13:54.070 --> 13:56.038
COME ON, IT'S TEA.

13:56.180 --> 13:58.102
THINK I DON'T KNOW
WHO I'M DEALING WITH?

13:58.250 --> 14:00.764
[clears throat]
HOW YOU FEELING?

14:00.900 --> 14:02.595
- TIRED AND SORE.

14:02.730 --> 14:06.279
AND I CAN'T DO THIS PUZZLE
WITH MY HAND LIKE THIS.

14:06.430 --> 14:09.069
- YOU KNOW, HONEY,
GARY'S GETTING A DUI,

14:09.220 --> 14:13.941
AND IT'S
PRETTY...SERIOUS.

14:14.090 --> 14:16.558
- [exhales]
OKAY.

14:19.130 --> 14:20.097
- HOW DO YOU FEEL?

14:20.230 --> 14:23.119
- OBVIOUSLY NOT GREAT.

14:23.270 --> 14:25.852
I MEAN, LOOK AT ME.
IT'S...

14:26.000 --> 14:27.683
- BUT WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?
I MEAN...

14:27.830 --> 14:30.037
- IT WAS AN ACCIDENT,
YOU KNOW?

14:30.170 --> 14:31.273
- BUT, AMBER,
THIS IS AN ACCIDENT

14:31.420 --> 14:33.138
THAT YOU ASKED FOR
IN A WAY.

14:33.280 --> 14:35.168
- WELL, I WASN'T DRIVING,
OKAY?

14:35.320 --> 14:37.038
AND I OBVIOUSLY
GOT REALLY MESSED UP.

14:37.180 --> 14:38.147
- BUT YOU GOT
IN THE CAR WITH SOMEONE

14:38.290 --> 14:39.666
WHO WAS CLEARLY...

14:39.800 --> 14:41.597
I MEAN, HIS BLOOD-ALCOHOL
WAS THROUGH THE ROOF.

14:41.740 --> 14:42.832
- I THOUGHT HE WAS FINE.

14:42.980 --> 14:44.049
- DO YOU UNDERSTAND
THAT--THAT--

14:44.190 --> 14:45.771
- I THINK I'VE
BEEN A'I'I'ACKED ENOUGH.

14:45.910 --> 14:47.320
- I'M NOT ATI'ACKING YOU.
- WHAT ARE YOU--

14:47.470 --> 14:49.222
- I'M AFRAID.
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IF--

14:49.370 --> 14:50.678
- MOM, SHE'S OBVIOUSLY
NOT EVEN LISTENING.

14:50.820 --> 14:51.957
- GET WHAT YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH.

14:52.090 --> 14:53.159
- WHAT THE HELL
IS YOUR PROBLEM NOW?

14:53.300 --> 14:54.710
- WHAT'S MY--
LOOK AT YOU.

14:54.850 --> 14:56.920
I MEAN, DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT YOU PUT US THROUGH?

14:57.060 --> 14:58.300
WHAT IF YOU HAD DIED?
- I GET IT.

14:58.440 --> 15:00.135
WHAT ELSE
DO YOU WANT ME TO SAY?

15:00.270 --> 15:01.168
- IT DOESN'T
SEEM LIKE YOU GET IT.

15:01.310 --> 15:02.891
- I DON'T WANNA TALK ABOUT IT.

15:03.040 --> 15:06.066
I GET IT.
OKAY?

15:06.210 --> 15:07.586
- ALL RIGHT.

15:14.840 --> 15:16.319
- OH, HEY, HONEY?

15:16.460 --> 15:18.109
I MADE THE APPOINTMENT--
- YEAH?

15:18.260 --> 15:21.115
- FOR MAX TO GET FI'I'I'ED
FOR A NEW RETAINER.

15:21.260 --> 15:22.704
- NEW RETAINER?
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE OLD ONE?

15:22.850 --> 15:24.158
- I TOLD YOU WE LOST IT,
REMEMBER?

15:24.300 --> 15:25.506
- NO.
- YEAH, I DID TELL--

15:25.640 --> 15:27.050
- YOU SAID
YOU COULDN'T FIND IT,

15:27.200 --> 15:28.053
MEANING THAT
YOU WERE GOING TO.

15:28.200 --> 15:29.713
- NO, THAT MEANS WE LOST IT.

15:29.850 --> 15:31.238
- KRISTINA,
THOSE THINGS ARE EXPENSIVE.

15:31.370 --> 15:34.134
LIKE $500.
- I AGREE, THEY'RE EXPEN--$700.

15:34.270 --> 15:35.544
- I DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW A SON LIKE OURS,

15:35.690 --> 15:37.203
WHO CAN REMEMBER
THE MOST MEANINGLESS FACTS,

15:37.350 --> 15:39.272
CAN'T REMEMBER
WHERE HE PUT HIS RETAINER.

15:39.420 --> 15:42.002
- I KNOW IT'S FRUSTRATING,
BUT IT HAPPENS, OKAY?

15:42.140 --> 15:43.584
- NO, YOU JUST GIVE ME SOME TIME
AND I'M GONNA FIND IT, OKAY?

15:43.730 --> 15:45.413
- I'VE ALREADY LOOKED.
- I SAID I'M GONNA FIND IT,

15:45.560 --> 15:47.312
I'M GONNA FIND IT.
- OKAY.

15:47.460 --> 15:50.736
WELL, GOOD LUCK WITH THAT.
I'VE LOOKED EVERYWHERE.

15:50.880 --> 15:54.259
ALSO, UM...

15:54.400 --> 15:56.846
I TOOK HADDIE
TO THE GYNECOLOGIST.

15:56.990 --> 15:59.220
- GREAT.

15:59.370 --> 16:02.362
- SHE'S OFFICIALLY ON
THE PILL.

16:04.410 --> 16:07.299
- SHE'S ON THE PILL.

16:07.440 --> 16:08.475
[sighs]

16:08.620 --> 16:11.202
ALL RIGHT, WELL.
HE STILL NEEDS TO WEAR A CONDOM.

16:11.340 --> 16:12.511
- I AGREE.
- YOU NEED TO TELL HER THAT.

16:12.660 --> 16:14.548
- I'LL TELL HER.
- 'CAUSE I KNOW HOW GUYS THINK.

16:14.690 --> 16:16.203
HE'S THINKING
THAT SHE'S ON THE PILL,

16:16.350 --> 16:17.169
SO HE DOESN'T
HAVE TO WEAR A CONDOM.

16:17.320 --> 16:20.209
- HONEY, I KNOW.
IT'S WEIRD.

16:23.010 --> 16:24.216
- MM-HMM!

16:24.360 --> 16:25.497
- WOULD YOU LIKE ANY MORE?

16:25.630 --> 16:26.972
- YES, PLEASE.

16:27.120 --> 16:28.394
- OH, WOULD YOU LIKE
A CUPCAKE?

16:28.530 --> 16:30.669
- YES.
- I WOULD LOVE A CUPCAKE.

16:30.810 --> 16:34.325
- THAT ONE DOES NOT MATCH,
BUT THIS ONE DOES.

16:34.470 --> 16:36.199
- THAT MATCHES?
- THAT MATCHES THE TEA.

16:36.340 --> 16:37.910
- IT MATCHES THE TEA.
WELL...

16:38.060 --> 16:39.334
- WELL, THAT'S WHAT I WANT.
- THAT'S A NO-BRAINER.

16:39.480 --> 16:41.641
- AND ANYTHING ELSE?
EXTRA LUMPS OR ANYTHING?

16:41.790 --> 16:43.826
- EXTRA LUMPS, YES.

16:43.960 --> 16:46.019
- JUST, LIKE, FIVE LUMPS.

16:46.170 --> 16:47.899
- OH, THIS IS ACTUALLY SUGAR.

16:48.040 --> 16:49.860
I CAN'T USE THAT.
- OKAY.

16:50.000 --> 16:51.137
- YEAH,
NO SUGAR, JUST LUMPS.

16:51.280 --> 16:54.147
- I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
- GREAT.

16:54.280 --> 16:55.383
- WE'LL BE HERE.

16:55.530 --> 16:58.215
- SO. ..
SO ANYWAY.

16:58.360 --> 17:00.908
YEAH, IT ENDED UP
BEING FINE.

17:01.050 --> 17:03.109
BUT IT WAS TOO LATE
TO GET HER AN EPIDURAL,

17:03.260 --> 17:05.012
AND SHE WAS
SCREAMING HYSTERICALLY.

17:05.160 --> 17:07.321
I MEAN, IT WAS--
SHE WAS IN SO MUCH PAIN.

17:07.470 --> 17:09.609
I FORGOT THE REALITY
OF GIVING BIRTH.

17:09.750 --> 17:12.332
- YEAH.
- ACTUALLY, I'M JUST GLAD

17:12.470 --> 17:15.928
THAT I DON'T HAVE
TO GO THROUGH THAT AGAIN.

17:16.060 --> 17:18.199
- YEAH.

17:18.340 --> 17:19.955
UH, IT'S GREAT THAT
YOU WERE THERE FOR HER.

17:20.100 --> 17:22.068
- WELL, THANKS.

17:22.210 --> 17:26.169
WE HAVE SUCH
AN AMAZING LIFE, JOEL.

17:26.320 --> 17:27.799
THE THREE OF US.

17:27.940 --> 17:31.103
DON'T NEED ANYTHING ELSE.

17:31.250 --> 17:33.184
VERY HAPPY.

17:33.320 --> 17:35.697
- WELL, HERE I COME.

17:35.840 --> 17:38.149
- HELLO!
- HELLO.

17:38.290 --> 17:40.429
- ALL RIGHT, UM...

17:40.570 --> 17:42.492
"SUDDENLY HANNAH'S FAMILY
MATERIALIZES

17:42.640 --> 17:44.460
SURROUNDING HER
ON THE COUCH."

17:44.610 --> 17:46.646
- THE COUCH OPENS OUT
INTO A BED.

17:46.780 --> 17:48.475
- REALLY? AWESOME.
- OH, JEEZ.

17:48.610 --> 17:50.953
- OH, MY GOD.
- DAD?

17:51.100 --> 17:54.206
- HONEY, YOU REALLY OUGHT
TO THINK THIS THING THROUGH.

17:54.340 --> 17:56.160
HE'S A MAILMAN.
- HEY, GUYS IN UNIFORM ARE CUTE.

17:56.310 --> 17:57.857
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

17:58.000 --> 17:59.649
- TRYING TO KEEP YOU
FROM MAKING A TERRIBLE MISTAKE.

17:59.800 --> 18:00.755
- WHY IS THERE NOTHING
IN THE FRIDGE?

18:00.900 --> 18:02.106
DON'T MAILM EN EAT?

18:02.250 --> 18:04.286
- HANNAH, YOU'RE
THROWING YOUR LIFE AWAY.

18:04.420 --> 18:07.241
- PAUL, DON'T--DON'T
COME DOWN SO HARD ON HER.

18:07.390 --> 18:10.109
- ME?
- LIKE WE TALKED ABOUT, YEAH.

18:10.260 --> 18:11.397
- GIL?
- WHY DON'T WE GET THROUGH

18:11.530 --> 18:13.225
THE PLAY ONCE
WITHOUT ANY INTERRUPTION?

18:13.360 --> 18:14.497
- YES.
- IT'S THE ONLY WAY

18:14.640 --> 18:17.256
WE'LL GET
A SENSE OF THE WHOLE.

18:17.400 --> 18:19.152
- HANNAH, YOU'RE THROWING
YOUR LIFE AWAY.

18:19.300 --> 18:20.983
- I'M LONELY, OKAY?

18:21.130 --> 18:22.267
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE
SUCH A SNOB.

18:22.410 --> 18:24.162
- OKAY, IF YOU
GO THROUGH WITH THIS,

18:24.310 --> 18:26.232
I OFFICIALLY GIVE UP.
I MEAN IT, HANNAH.

18:26.380 --> 18:28.757
IT'S OVER.
- YOU JUDGING ME IS OVER?

18:28.900 --> 18:31.300
- CAN'T YOU SEE THAT EVERYTHING
I DO IS ONLY TRYING TO HELP?

18:31.450 --> 18:33.793
BUT YOU NEVER SEEM TO GET THAT.
I WORKED SO HARD,

18:33.940 --> 18:36.135
AND YOU CONTINUE TO
THROW YOUR LIFE DOWN THE TOILET.

18:36.280 --> 18:37.656
- PAUL, I'M SO SORRY.
I JUST WANT--

18:37.800 --> 18:39.279
I DON'T WANT YOU TO
GET STUCK DOING IT THIS WAY.

18:39.420 --> 18:40.694
'CAUSE, UM--
LET ME SEE IF I CAN--

18:40.840 --> 18:42.148
- YOU KNOW THIS
IS A READ-THROUGH, RIGHT?

18:42.290 --> 18:43.598
- NO, NO--
- LET'S JUST TAKE FIVE.

18:43.740 --> 18:45.321
- I DON'T WANNA DEAL WITH THIS.
- I'M JUST TRYING

18:45.460 --> 18:46.700
TO GET IT RIGHT.
- I APPRECIATE THE OPPORTUNITY,

18:46.840 --> 18:48.705
GIL, I REALLY DO,
BUT LIFE IS TOO SHORT.

18:48.850 --> 18:50.806
- I--WHY ARE ACTORS
SO SENSITIVE?

18:50.950 --> 18:52.599
- I'M NOT BEING SENSITIVE.

18:52.750 --> 18:54.638
- I'M JUST TRYING TO
GET IT THE WAY IT SHOULD BE.

18:54.780 --> 18:56.600
- I'M SORRY,
YOUR PLAY'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH

18:56.750 --> 18:59.401
FOR ME TO PUT UP WITH YOU.
- SHUT UP PLEASE AND BE QUIET!

18:59.550 --> 19:01.165
AND I THINK
I NEED FIVE MINUTES OFF.

19:01.310 --> 19:02.402
- I'M TAKING FIVE.
I'M TAKING FIVE.

19:02.550 --> 19:04.927
- ARE WE DONE?
- WELL, THIS IS A BLAST.

19:05.070 --> 19:07.061
- SARAH, SARAH, PLEASE.
- I JUST NEED A MINUTE, DAD.

19:07.210 --> 19:08.654
- HOLD UP, BABY.

19:08.800 --> 19:10.552
GOD.
SARAH...

19:10.700 --> 19:14.170
HONEY, LOOK.
REALLY, HOLD.

19:14.320 --> 19:16.288
I REALLY THINK
YOU KINDA LET THE ACTORS

19:16.430 --> 19:17.454
GO THROUGH IT
A COUPLE OF TIMES,

19:17.600 --> 19:18.942
BEFORE YOU START--
- I KNOW, I KNOW.

19:19.080 --> 19:21.184
DAD, I'M COMPLETELY...

19:21.330 --> 19:22.911
I'M--YOU KNOW...

19:23.050 --> 19:26.599
I'M, LIKE, NUMB INSIDE.
I DON'T EVEN KNOW...

19:26.750 --> 19:29.878
I JUST KEEP THINKING
OF WHAT COULD'VE HAPPENED.

19:30.030 --> 19:33.090
AND YOU KNOW,
I COULD HAVE LOST HER.

19:33.240 --> 19:36.368
I DON'T THINK SHE LEARNED
ANYTHING FROM THAT ACCIDENT.

19:36.520 --> 19:38.306
AND I'M JUST...

19:38.450 --> 19:40.680
I'M TERRIFIED THAT--
I'M TERRIFIED.

19:53.910 --> 19:57.289
- HEY.

19:57.430 --> 19:59.182
YOU SHOW HER THE PLACE?

19:59.330 --> 20:03.812
- UH...YEAH,
SHE HASN'T COME OVER.

20:05.890 --> 20:07.505
- [sighs]

20:07.650 --> 20:10.574
[The Walkmen's
While I Shovel The Snow]

20:12.310 --> 20:14.232
- WELL, THEY SAY

20:14.380 --> 20:16.996
CAN'T PLEASE EVERYONE

20:17.140 --> 20:18.584
BUT I'M STUCK

20:18.730 --> 20:20.106
- THANKS FOR
LETTING ME COME OVER.

20:20.250 --> 20:23.219
- ON A WINNING STREAK
- YOU SAID IT WAS URGENT.

20:23.360 --> 20:26.215
- UM...

20:26.360 --> 20:29.215
UM, I JUST WANNA SAY SORRY.

20:29.360 --> 20:32.158
I'M SORRY
WE FOUGHT OVER DISHES,

20:32.300 --> 20:36.464
AND I'M SORRY
I HAD AN AFFAIR.

20:36.610 --> 20:39.579
I'M SORRY I DID THAT
TO YOU AND OUR SON.

20:42.820 --> 20:43.889
I LOVE YOU,

20:44.030 --> 20:46.999
AND I'M ALWAYS
GONNA BE THERE FOR JABBAR.

20:50.420 --> 20:52.240
AND I WISH THERE
WAS SOMETHING I COULD DO

20:52.380 --> 20:54.416
TO MAKE EVERYTHING RIGHT,
YOU KNOW?

20:54.560 --> 20:57.108
SAY SOMETHING MAGICAL,
OR BUY YOU A HOUSE.

20:57.250 --> 21:01.357
BUT...
IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

21:01.500 --> 21:05.254
AND I DON'T WANT YOU
TO FEEL WEIRD AROUND ME.

21:05.400 --> 21:08.699
I SCREWED UP.
IT'S ALL ME.

21:11.200 --> 21:14.226
AND I WANT YOU
TO FEEL FREEDOM,

21:14.370 --> 21:17.430
MOVE ON WITH YOUR LIFE.

21:19.550 --> 21:22.758
I'M NOT GONNA
PURSUE YOU ANYMORE.

21:22.900 --> 21:27.655
UM...

21:27.800 --> 21:29.654
THAT'S IT.

21:33.050 --> 21:35.939
- [sighs]

21:38.360 --> 21:41.181
[knock at door]

21:41.330 --> 21:43.798
- CAN YOU PUT YOUR BOOK DOWN
AND GIVE ME YOUR ATTENTION?

21:43.950 --> 21:45.326
MAX?
- DID YOU KNOW THAT THERE ARE

21:45.470 --> 21:47.222
SCORPIONS THAT CAN
SURVIVE ON ONLY ONE MEAL

21:47.370 --> 21:50.578
FOR THE WHOLE YEAR?

21:50.720 --> 21:52.745
- NO.
I DID NOT KNOW THAT.

21:52.890 --> 21:54.949
NOW, LISTEN, RIGHT NOW WE'RE NOT
GONNA TALK ABOUT BUGS, OKAY?

21:55.100 --> 21:58.206
WE ARE GOING TO FIGURE OUT
WHERE YOUR RETAINER IS.

21:58.350 --> 22:00.033
- IT'S LOST.
- I KNOW IT'S LOST, MAX,

22:00.180 --> 22:02.489
BUT IT HASN'T DISAPPEARED
FOREVER, RIGHT?

22:02.630 --> 22:04.279
NOW LET'S USE
THAT GOOD MEMORY OF YOURS.

22:04.420 --> 22:06.103
[sighs]
MAX.

22:06.250 --> 22:07.660
- DAD, HEY!

22:07.800 --> 22:08.971
- I JUST NEED YOU TO
SHIl-T YOUR FOCUS, OKAY?

22:09.120 --> 22:11.327
- DAD, THAT'S NOT WHERE IT GOES!
- WE'LL GET IT IN A MINUTE.

22:11.460 --> 22:12.563
I NEED YOU
TO JUST FOCUS, OKAY?

22:12.710 --> 22:14.041
- I ALREADY TALKED
ABOUT THIS WITH MOM.

22:14.190 --> 22:15.600
- I KNOW YOU TALKED ABOUT IT
WITH YOUR MOTHER,

22:15.740 --> 22:16.729
BUT NOW YOU'RE
GONNA TALK ABOUT IT WITH ME.

22:16.880 --> 22:18.393
WHERE'S THE LAST PLACE
YOU SAW YOUR RETAINER?

22:18.540 --> 22:20.292
- IF I KNEW THAT,
THEN I'D KNOW WHERE IT WAS,

22:20.440 --> 22:21.771
AND WE'D FIND IT.
- YES, MAX.

22:21.920 --> 22:22.989
THAT'S A VERY GOOD POINT.
LET'S THINK OF ALL

22:23.130 --> 22:24.677
THE PLACES YOU WERE
THE DAY YOU LOST IT.

22:24.820 --> 22:26.196
WE'LL MAKE A LIST.
WE'LL DO IT TOGETHER, ALL RIGHT?

22:26.340 --> 22:27.955
LET ME GRAB A PEN.
MAX!

22:28.100 --> 22:29.897
ALL RIGHT, TELL YOU WHAT,
YOU CAN HAVE YOUR BOOK, OKAY?

22:30.030 --> 22:31.679
- NO, DAD, THAT PEN'S
NOT FOR WRITING.

22:31.830 --> 22:33.104
THAT PEN IS FOR COLORING!
- MAX, I'LL PUT IT RIGHT BACK.

22:33.240 --> 22:35.242
- THAT'S NOT WHAT THIS--
- YOU WERE IN YOUR ROOM...

22:35.380 --> 22:36.722
YOU WERE IN THE KITCHEN.
- CAN'T YOU JUST

22:36.870 --> 22:38.007
BUY ANOTHER ONE?
- NO, WE CAN'T.

22:38.140 --> 22:40.176
THEY'RE $700, MAX!
- THEN GO TO THE ATM!

22:40.320 --> 22:42.106
- YOU CAN'T JUST GO
TO AN ATM AND GET MONEY--

22:42.250 --> 22:43.387
MAX, LET GO.

22:43.530 --> 22:44.974
MAX, I WANT YOU
TO SIT DOWN RIGHT NOW.

22:45.120 --> 22:48.146
MAX, SIT DOWN!

22:48.290 --> 22:51.839
[sighs]

22:51.990 --> 22:55.812
- ARE YOU...MAD AT ME
BECAUSE I HAVE ASPERGER'S?

23:02.340 --> 23:03.955
- NO, MAX, I'M NOT--

23:04.100 --> 23:06.728
I'M NOT MAD AT YOU
BECAUSE YOU HAVE ASPERGER'S.

23:06.860 --> 23:09.727
NEVER.

23:16.290 --> 23:17.359
[sighs]

23:17.490 --> 23:19.765
[seagulls screeching]

23:19.910 --> 23:21.184
- SO...

23:21.330 --> 23:24.356
WHAT'S THIS ALL ABOUT?

23:24.500 --> 23:28.846
- I WANT YOU
TO SEE SOMETHING.

23:28.990 --> 23:31.959
- [sighs]

23:36.060 --> 23:37.504
- RECOGNIZE IT?

23:37.650 --> 23:42.303
- [sniffs]
YEAH, IT'S...THE CAR.

23:42.450 --> 23:43.826
IT'S GARY'S CAR.

23:43.970 --> 23:47.178
- MM-HMM.

23:47.320 --> 23:50.175
COME HERE.
TAKE A LOOK.

23:52.740 --> 23:56.187
YOU LOOKIN'?

23:56.330 --> 23:58.594
- YEAH.
I SEE IT.

23:59.740 --> 24:01.674
- AMBER...

24:01.810 --> 24:07.157
YOU KNOW, I WAS
TWO YEARS IN VIETNAM.

24:07.300 --> 24:10.269
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT I THOUGHT ABOUT?

24:10.410 --> 24:12.514
WHAT I DREAMT ABOUT?

24:12.650 --> 24:15.164
WAS COMING HOME.

24:15.310 --> 24:18.177
AND HAVING A FAMILY.

24:18.310 --> 24:20.699
HAVING GRANDKIDS.

24:20.830 --> 24:23.867
I DREAMT YOU, AMBER.

24:27.390 --> 24:29.631
AND HADDIE.

24:29.770 --> 24:34.082
AND DREW.
AND SYDNEY.
JABBAR.

24:34.230 --> 24:37.882
AND MAX.

24:38.020 --> 24:40.295
AND WE ALMOST LOST YOU, AMBER.

24:40.440 --> 24:44.126
I KNOW YOU'VE HAD
SOME BAD BREAKS.

24:44.270 --> 24:46.682
NOT FEELING
GOOD ABOUT YOURSELF.

24:46.830 --> 24:48.377
YOU DIDN'T
GET INTO BERKELEY.

24:48.520 --> 24:52.650
WELL, BOO-FREAKING-HOO.

24:52.800 --> 24:56.031
YOU GOTTA
SUCK IT UP, GIRL.

24:56.180 --> 24:58.319
YOU'RE A BRAVERMAN.

24:58.460 --> 25:02.009
YOU GOT MY BLOOD
IN YOUR VEINS.

25:02.150 --> 25:04.118
YOU EVER DO
SOMETHING LIKE THIS AGAIN--

25:04.260 --> 25:07.081
YOU EVEN THINKABOUT
DOING SOMETHING LIKE THIS,

25:07.220 --> 25:09.256
I WILL PERSONALLY
KICK YOUR LITTLE BUTT

25:09.400 --> 25:12.506
ALL THE WAY FROM HERE
TO THE GOLDEN GATE BRIDGE.

25:14.370 --> 25:18.124
YOU DO NOT HAVE MY PERMISSION
TO MESS WITH MY DREAMS.

25:18.270 --> 25:22.229
ARE WE CLEAR?

25:22.380 --> 25:24.098
- [sobbing]

25:24.240 --> 25:26.060
I'M SORRY.

25:26.210 --> 25:32.103
[crying]

25:32.250 --> 25:35.242
I'M SORRY.

25:35.390 --> 25:40.566
[crying]

25:40.710 --> 25:42.325
- GOOD.

25:42.470 --> 25:45.564
- [crying]

25:48.750 --> 25:51.787
- I'LL BUY YOU A BURGER.

26:00.350 --> 26:01.442
[knock at door]

26:01.590 --> 26:03.137
- HEY.

26:05.180 --> 26:08.559
UH, LISTEN, CORY,
I JUST WANNA CLEAR THE AIR.

26:08.700 --> 26:10.520
I'M REALLY SORRY
FOR LOSING IT.

26:10.670 --> 26:12.183
I HAD NO RIGHT TO DO THAT.

26:12.320 --> 26:15.255
I JUST HAD A LATE NIGHT,
WAS AT THE HOSPITAL, AND...

26:15.400 --> 26:16.708
LOOK, THE TRUTH IS,

26:16.850 --> 26:18.226
NO MATTER
WHAT I FEEL ABOUT EDDIE,

26:18.360 --> 26:20.009
THIS IS YOUR COMPANY,
YOU HAVE EVERY RIGHT TO HIRE

26:20.160 --> 26:22.219
AND FIRE WHOEVER YOU WANT
WITHOUT CONSULTING ME.

26:22.370 --> 26:24.463
I JUST WISH YOU WOULD.

26:24.610 --> 26:27.261
I WAS OUT OF LINE,
SO I'M SORRY.

26:28.960 --> 26:30.370
- YOU'RE NOT HAPPY HERE,
ADAM.

26:30.510 --> 26:31.681
- WHAT?

26:31.830 --> 26:33.400
- AT THIS JOB.
ARE YOU?

26:33.550 --> 26:34.824
- I'M FINE.
IT'S FINE.

26:34.970 --> 26:38.440
- I FEEL LIKE ANY TIME
I DO SOMETHING--

26:38.590 --> 26:40.103
CHOOSE A NEW DIRECTION...
- MM-HMM.

26:40.250 --> 26:41.729
- EXPRESS MYSELF,

26:41.870 --> 26:44.430
I FEEL LIKE
YOU'RE JUST JUDGING ME...

26:44.560 --> 26:46.949
AS OPPOSED TO JOINING ME.

26:47.080 --> 26:50.117
- I'M NOT, I'M--
- AND THAT REALLY HURTS, MAN.

26:50.260 --> 26:52.046
TRUTH BE TOLD.
- OKAY.

26:52.190 --> 26:54.670
- IT MAKES IT
REALLY HARD FOR ME.

26:54.820 --> 26:57.607
I REALLY RESPECT YOU
AND THE WORK THAT YOU DO.

26:57.750 --> 27:00.093
- THANK YOU.

27:00.230 --> 27:03.165
- BUT I JUST DON'T THINK
THIS IS A GOOD FIT FOR YOU.

27:12.830 --> 27:14.411
- ARE YOU FIRING ME?

27:17.320 --> 27:20.312
- I'M LETTING YOU GO.
- OH.

27:25.600 --> 27:27.465
UGH.
[sighs]

27:27.610 --> 27:30.124
- I'M REALLY SORRY, MAN.

27:48.700 --> 27:50.861
- TH ERE'S--
TH ERE'S AUNT SARAH.

27:51.010 --> 27:53.046
- HI.
- HI.

27:53.180 --> 27:55.694
- OH!
SO GLAD TO SEE YOU.

27:55.840 --> 27:57.319
I'M REALLY NERVOUS.
- I'M NOT NERVOUS.

27:57.460 --> 27:59.519
- OKAY, GOOD.
WELL, YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE.

27:59.670 --> 28:02.047
JUST DON'T LIE
IF YOU DON'T LIKE IT, OKAY?

28:02.190 --> 28:03.919
- DON'T LIE?
- NO.

28:04.060 --> 28:05.573
- TRUTH?
- YES.

28:05.710 --> 28:08.190
- HEY.

28:08.340 --> 28:10.399
I'M SORRY.

28:10.550 --> 28:14.236
I'M REALLY SORRY.

28:14.380 --> 28:17.235
FOR BEING SO STUPID.

28:18.550 --> 28:20.131
DO YOU THINK THAT YOU COULD

28:20.280 --> 28:22.134
PLEASE FORGIVE ME NOW
AND BE MY FRIEND?

28:22.280 --> 28:25.272
BECAUSE
I DON'T LIKE ANYBODY ELSE.

28:27.290 --> 28:30.566
- YEAH, I THINK
I CAN BE YOUR FRIEND.

28:30.700 --> 28:32.144
- [giggIeS]
- [chuckles]

28:32.290 --> 28:34.736
- THANK YOU.
I FEEL BETTER ALREADY.

28:34.880 --> 28:36.871
- IS IT SOLD OUT NOW?

28:37.020 --> 28:39.193
- I DON'T KNOW. NO.
BUT IT'S FULL.

28:39.330 --> 28:40.888
OKAY, I HAVE TO GO CHECK
BACKSTAGE, ACTUALLY.

28:41.020 --> 28:42.499
- OKAY.
- BUT I'LL SEE YOU IN THE HOUSE.

28:42.650 --> 28:43.810
- YES, YOU WILL, YOU BETTER.
- I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

28:43.960 --> 28:46.428
- DON'T DITCH US.
[laughter]

28:46.580 --> 28:47.956
- MIDSUMMER NIGHT'S DREAM?

28:48.100 --> 28:50.091
- MAX...
NO, I DON'T.

28:50.240 --> 28:52.617
- HADDIE, HONEY, DO YOU
HAVE YOUR CELL PHONE WITH YOU?

28:52.760 --> 28:54.102
- NO, I FORGOT.
- WE'RE LATE.

28:54.240 --> 28:57.243
- SHE HAS TO FIGHT GIDEON.
I CAN'T BELIEVE I FORGOT THAT.

28:57.390 --> 28:59.278
- YEAH.
BUT THEN, WHAT DO THEY CALL--

28:59.420 --> 29:01.149
- HEY, HOW ARE YOU GUYS?
- HI.

29:01.290 --> 29:02.837
HOW WAS WORK?
- UH...

29:02.980 --> 29:04.948
IT WAS...QUITE A DAY.

29:05.080 --> 29:07.014
- GOOD.
GOOD.

29:07.150 --> 29:08.469
- HEY, GOT YOUR FAVORITE.
CANDY.

29:08.600 --> 29:09.589
[chatter overlaps]

29:09.740 --> 29:10.877
- ALL RIGHT,
LET'S JUST GO IN.

29:11.020 --> 29:12.772
- CANDY, THANK YOU, ALEX.
- COME ON, GUYS.

29:12.920 --> 29:15.468
LET'S GO.
- MR. BRAVERMAN?

29:15.610 --> 29:17.123
- YEAH.
- HEY, UM...

29:17.270 --> 29:20.785
I JUST WANTED
TO LET YOU KNOW THAT

29:20.930 --> 29:22.090
I LOVE YOUR DAUGHTER,

29:22.240 --> 29:26.233
AND I WILL ALWAYS
RESPECT HER.

29:26.380 --> 29:27.756
- ANYTHING ELSE?

29:27.900 --> 29:29.822
- NOPE.
JUST--JUST--JUST--

29:29.970 --> 29:32.313
GUESS THAT'S IT.

29:34.390 --> 29:37.279
- WEAR A CONDOM.

29:38.910 --> 29:41.117
- YES, SIR.

29:47.370 --> 29:48.769
- WHAT?

29:48.920 --> 29:50.057
- THAT'S
WHAT I'M HOPING FOR.

29:50.200 --> 29:51.360
SO THANK YOU,
THANK YOU.

29:51.510 --> 29:53.228
- YOU'RE NOT GONNA EAT
ALL THAT CANDY.

29:53.370 --> 29:54.576
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?
- AUNT SARAH.

29:54.720 --> 29:56.062
- HEY.
- HEY, SARAH.

29:56.200 --> 29:57.883
- I'M REALLY SORRY FOR
WHAT I SAID AT THE HOSPITAL.

29:58.030 --> 30:01.090
I HAVE ASPERGER'S.

30:05.070 --> 30:08.142
- THAT'S OKAY, MAX.
THANKS.

30:08.280 --> 30:10.589
- AND I'M ALSO REALLY GLAD
THAT AMBER DIDN'T DIE.

30:10.730 --> 30:13.767
AND ALSO, IF SHE DID, YOU
WOULD'VE HAD TO GO TO A FUNERAL

30:13.910 --> 30:16.049
AND WOULD PROBABLY BE
TOO SAD TO COME HERE TODAY.

30:16.190 --> 30:18.044
AND WE WOULDN'T BE HERE.

30:18.190 --> 30:19.532
- THAT'S REALLY TRUE.

30:19.670 --> 30:22.605
YOU KNOW, MAX,
THIS IS A BIG NIGHT FOR ME,

30:22.750 --> 30:23.910
AND I'M REALLY NERVOUS.

30:24.060 --> 30:25.129
WOULD YOU MIND
SITTING NEXT TO ME?

30:25.270 --> 30:26.430
- SURE.
- AWESOME.

30:26.580 --> 30:28.229
OKAY, OUR SEATS
ARE B-107 AND B-108.

30:28.370 --> 30:30.099
- OKAY.
- YOU REMEMBER THAT?

30:30.240 --> 30:31.264
- SURE.
- WHO AM I ASKING?

30:31.410 --> 30:32.229
OF COURSE.
OKAY, I'LL SEE YOU.

30:32.380 --> 30:33.586
- BREAK A LEG.
- THANKS.

30:33.720 --> 30:36.166
- YEAH, BREAK A LEG.
- WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

30:36.310 --> 30:38.995
IF SHE BROKE A LEG--
- IT'S JUST AN EXPRESSION, MAX.

30:39.140 --> 30:41.199
- BUT THAT'S
A TERRIBLE THEATRE EXPRESSION.

30:45.560 --> 30:47.733
[floorboards creak]
- [gasps] OH! HI.

30:47.880 --> 30:48.869
IT'S SO FULL.

30:49.010 --> 30:50.523
- SARAH.
- YEAH?

30:50.670 --> 30:53.707
- I JUST--I WANTED TO APOLOGIZE
ABOUT THE REHEARSAL EARLIER.

30:53.850 --> 30:55.602
- YEAH, NO, ME TOO.
- THANKS.

30:55.750 --> 30:58.537
I HAVE A LOT GOING ON.
THANKS FOR COMING BACK.

30:58.680 --> 31:01.126
- NO, I JUST WANNA SAY
THAT THESE WORDS ARE INCREDIBLE.

31:01.270 --> 31:04.398
AND I'M GONNA DO EVERYTHING
I CAN TO DO THEM JUSTICE.

31:04.550 --> 31:05.858
- GOD. THANKS, PAUL.
- THANK YOU.

31:06.000 --> 31:07.137
- WOW.
OKAY, THANKS.

31:07.270 --> 31:09.374
- BREAK A LEG TONIGHT?
- SURE, YEAH.

31:09.520 --> 31:10.509
- OKAY, GOOD.
- THANK YOU.

31:10.660 --> 31:12.059
- YOU'RE THE BEST.

31:12.210 --> 31:14.440
YOU GUYS LOVE TO HUG.
ACTORS LOVE TO HUG.

31:14.590 --> 31:15.898
- WE'RE GONNA DO A GREAT JOB.
- THANK YOU.

31:16.040 --> 31:17.837
- WE'RE GONNA KNOCK THEM DEAD.
- OKAY.

31:17.970 --> 31:19.289
OH, OKAY.
- IT'S A PRIVILEGE.

31:19.420 --> 31:20.352
THANK YOU.
- THANK YOU.

31:20.490 --> 31:22.139
- ARE YOU NERVOUS?
- YEAH.

31:22.290 --> 31:23.143
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT A THING,
HONEY.

31:23.290 --> 31:25.144
ZEEK BRAVERMAN'S
PLAYING BARRY.

31:25.290 --> 31:26.700
- [laughing]
GO GET 'EM, DAD.

31:26.850 --> 31:29.364
- OKAY.
- WOW.

31:29.500 --> 31:32.321
EVERYONE'S SO NICE.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

31:32.470 --> 31:34.392
- I TOLD THEM
YOUR DAUGHTER DIED.

31:34.540 --> 31:36.223
- WHAT?

31:39.100 --> 31:41.785
- YOU KNOW, THE COUCH
OPENS UP INTO A BED.

31:41.930 --> 31:43.579
- REALLY?

31:43.720 --> 31:46.234
WELL, I GUESS IT DOESN'T
OPEN OUT ON ITS OWN.

31:46.380 --> 31:48.757
[laughter]
- YOU KNOW, YOU'RE REALLY COOL.

31:48.900 --> 31:50.458
- THANK YOU.
- I'VE BEEN DELIVERING PACKAGES

31:50.590 --> 31:52.797
FOR SIX YEARS,
AND I'VE NEVER HOOKED UP

31:52.940 --> 31:55.044
WITH ANYBODY WHO'S
ANSWERED THE DOOR, YOU KNOW?

31:55.180 --> 31:56.522
- UM, WOW.
THANK YOU.

31:56.670 --> 31:58.809
[chuckles]
HOW ABOUT WE JUST DON'T TALK?

31:58.950 --> 32:00.144
[audience ohs]

32:00.290 --> 32:02.565
NOT TALKING
WOULD JUST BE SO GREAT.

32:02.710 --> 32:03.734
- RIGHT ON.

32:03.880 --> 32:05.154
SO YOU WANNA DO IT?

32:05.300 --> 32:06.369
- TOTALLY.
- YEAH.

32:06.510 --> 32:08.978
- AH, JEEZ.
- DAD?

32:09.130 --> 32:11.598
- THE GUY PLAYING DAD
DOESN'T LOOK ANYTHING LIKE DAD.

32:11.750 --> 32:13.365
- YOU GOTTA THINK THIS THROUGH,
SWEETHEART.

32:13.510 --> 32:15.990
HE'S A MAILMAN.
- HEY, GUYS IN UNIFORM ARE CUTE.

32:16.140 --> 32:17.584
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

32:17.720 --> 32:20.348
- TRYING TO KEEP YOU
FROM MAKING A TERRIBLE MISTAKE.

32:20.490 --> 32:21.969
- IT'S NOT
THE FIRST ONE, EITHER.

32:22.110 --> 32:23.691
- WELL, THIS IS
SO NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

32:23.830 --> 32:25.240
GOD, JUST GET OUT OF HERE.

32:25.390 --> 32:26.903
- HAPPY TO.
THIS IS GROSSING ME OUT.

32:27.040 --> 32:28.450
- GOOD JOB, GRANDPA.

32:28.600 --> 32:30.488
- YOU READY, CUTIE?
- NO.

32:30.630 --> 32:33.042
- HUH?
- OH, I'M SORRY, YES.

32:33.190 --> 32:34.396
I MEAN, YES.
[giggIeS]

32:34.530 --> 32:36.009
- COME ON,
THAT'S ALL IT TAKES?

32:36.160 --> 32:37.639
"YOU READY?"

32:37.780 --> 32:39.498
GOOD GOD, WE RAISED YOU
BETTER THAN THAT.

32:39.640 --> 32:40.982
- YOU KNOW,
I'M LONELY, OKAY?

32:41.130 --> 32:42.392
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO BE SUCH A SNOB.

32:42.540 --> 32:44.337
- HEY, HEY, HEY,
I'M LONELY TOO, BABY.

32:44.470 --> 32:46.358
[laughter]

32:49.650 --> 32:51.402
- HEY, SWEETIE.
EVERYTHING OKAY?

32:51.550 --> 32:53.302
- [sobbing] I'M FINE.
GO IN--GO BACK IN.

32:53.450 --> 32:55.304
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.
- YOU FEELING OKAY?

32:55.450 --> 32:57.827
- I'M FINE.
I'M JUST FEELING EMOTIONAL.

32:57.970 --> 33:00.279
- WHAT'S THE MATTER?
HONEY!

33:00.420 --> 33:02.559
- I'M SORRY THAT
I PUT YOU THROUGH THAT.

33:02.700 --> 33:07.148
AND I LOVE YOU, AND I PROMISE
I'LL BE SAFE AND SMART.

33:07.290 --> 33:08.427
- THAT'S ALL
I WAS WORRIED ABOUT.

33:08.570 --> 33:10.083
THAT'S ALL
I WAS WORRIED ABOUT.

33:10.220 --> 33:11.255
- I'M SORRY,
I'M SO SCARED.

33:11.400 --> 33:13.254
AND JUST
LOOKING AT EVERYBODY HERE

33:13.400 --> 33:15.220
AND THINKING THAT
I COULDN'T SEE THEM AGAIN

33:15.370 --> 33:17.679
AND I COULDN'T BE HERE
AND SEE YOUR PLAY.

33:17.820 --> 33:19.026
LOOK WHAT YOU DID.

33:19.160 --> 33:20.673
THERE'S PEOPLE,
AND THEY LOVE IT.

33:20.820 --> 33:22.333
AND I'M SO PROUD OF YOU.

33:22.480 --> 33:25.301
AND YOU--YOU SAY YOU
DON'T WANT ME TO BE LIKE YOU,

33:25.450 --> 33:27.850
BUT I WANNA BE LIKE THIS.

33:28.000 --> 33:30.104
THIS IS AMAZING
WHAT YOU'VE DONE.

33:30.240 --> 33:31.275
- I DON'T KNOW
WHETHER TO HUG YOU

33:31.420 --> 33:32.375
BECAUSE
I DON'T WANNA HURT YOU.

33:32.520 --> 33:34.556
- I'M SO PROUD OF YOU.
- OH, HONEY.

33:34.700 --> 33:36.588
THANK YOU
FOR TELLING ME THAT.

33:36.730 --> 33:37.719
I LOVE YOU.

33:37.870 --> 33:40.111
I WAS SO WORRIED ABOUT YOU,
YOU KNOW?

33:40.250 --> 33:41.251
- I KNOW.
I'M SORRY.

33:41.390 --> 33:43.802
- I'M SO GLAD YOU'RE OKAY.

33:45.880 --> 33:47.461
- OKAY, I DON'T
WANNA MISS THE ENDING,

33:47.610 --> 33:50.249
SO I'M GONNA GO BACK IN.
[both laughing]

33:50.400 --> 33:52.504
- REALLY? YOU WANNA GO
TO THE BATHROOM OR SOMETHING?

33:52.650 --> 33:54.914
- NO.
I LOOK GREAT.

33:55.060 --> 33:57.779
- SO, COLBY, YOU STILL
GOIN' OUT WITH THE STRIPPER?

33:57.930 --> 34:00.239
- OKAY, ALL RIGHT.
NOW, SHE IS NOT A STRIPPER.

34:00.380 --> 34:02.894
SHE DOES BURLESQUE.
THERE IS A DIFFERENCE.

34:03.040 --> 34:05.065
- HE LOOKS SO MUCH LIKE YOU
WITHOUT MY GLASSES.

34:05.210 --> 34:06.518
- YOU HAVE
A LOW OPINION OF ME.

34:06.660 --> 34:09.003
- I DON'T THINK
THIS TREE HOUSE CAN HOLD US ALL.

34:09.150 --> 34:11.596
- OH, COME ON, DAD BUILT IT.
- YOU JUST MADE MY POINT.

34:11.730 --> 34:13.174
- HE JUST
HAS THE SAME HAIRCUT.

34:13.320 --> 34:14.730
- NO,
YOU HAVE BETTER HAIR.

34:14.880 --> 34:16.939
- IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY TODAY
FOR BASEBALL, FOLKS.

34:17.080 --> 34:18.286
WE'VE GOT
THE HOME TEAM RETURNING

34:18.430 --> 34:20.603
FROM A SIX-GAME ROAD TRIP.

34:20.740 --> 34:22.116
YOU KNOW, THE FIRST TIME
I SAW YOUR MOTHER,

34:22.260 --> 34:23.181
WE WERE AT A BASEBALL GAME.

34:23.330 --> 34:25.264
- YEAH, I KNOW, DAD.
- YEP.

34:25.400 --> 34:27.641
I KNOW YOU KNOW.
I KNOW I'VE TOLD YOU BEFORE.

34:27.780 --> 34:28.986
I WAN NA TALK ABOUT
YOUR MOTHER.

34:29.130 --> 34:32.714
I MEAN, SO SUE ME.

34:32.860 --> 34:35.169
- I LOVE YOU, DAD.

34:35.310 --> 34:37.995
- YEAH.
YEAH.

34:38.140 --> 34:41.029
[applause]

34:41.180 --> 34:42.727
[Bowerbirds'
House of Diamonds]

34:42.870 --> 34:44.861
- YOU ARE
FREE FROM THE LUST

34:45.010 --> 34:46.898
FOR THE LUSTER

34:47.050 --> 34:49.075
OF THE DIAMOND HOUSES

34:49.220 --> 34:52.257
IN THE CITY'S CLUSTER

34:52.400 --> 34:56.564
FROM YOUR OWN EGO
- AUTHOR!

34:56.710 --> 34:59.702
AUTHOR!
- FROM YOUR OWN BLUNDER

34:59.850 --> 35:01.841
[cheers and applause]

35:01.990 --> 35:06.996
YES, YOU OWN THE STARS,
YOU OWN THE THUNDER

35:07.130 --> 35:10.133
BUT YOU HAVE TO SHARE

35:10.280 --> 35:14.171
YES, YOU OWN THE STARS...
- DAD, BE COOL.

35:14.310 --> 35:15.823
- WAY TO GO.

35:15.970 --> 35:18.200
BUT YOU HAVE TO SHARE

35:18.350 --> 35:21.934
YOU ARE FREE

35:22.080 --> 35:24.457
YOU ARE ALREADY FREE

35:24.600 --> 35:31.290
YOU ARE
AL-L-L-L-L-L-READY FREE

35:35.580 --> 35:37.400
- THAT'S A BIG SMILE.

35:37.540 --> 35:39.576
- WHAT DO BABIES
DREAM ABOUT?

35:39.720 --> 35:41.369
- OH, I DON'T KNOW,
BABY THINGS.

35:41.510 --> 35:44.024
CUTE LITTLE BABY THINGS.
- NO LIFE EXPERIENCE.

35:44.170 --> 35:45.853
- UM...
- OH, MY GOD.

35:46.000 --> 35:47.206
- HI.
- HI.

35:47.350 --> 35:48.442
- GOD, DIDN'T WANNA
INTERRUPT FAMILY TIME.

35:48.590 --> 35:50.410
- GET IN HERE.
HONEY, THIS IS JULIA.

35:50.560 --> 35:51.959
SHE'S THE ONE
WHO DID YOUR JOB.

35:52.110 --> 35:53.725
- THANK YOU SO MUCH.

35:53.870 --> 35:55.246
YOU'RE LIKE A ROCK STAR
AROUND HERE.

35:55.390 --> 35:56.459
- YEAH, NO PROBLEM.

35:56.600 --> 35:58.807
WELL, I CAME
TO BRING YOU THIS.

35:58.940 --> 36:00.214
I DON'T NEED IT ANYMORE.

36:00.360 --> 36:03.079
- YEAH, I TOLD HER
WE DIDN'T HAVE A CAR SEAT

36:03.230 --> 36:05.539
BECAUSE I WAS INSANE.

36:05.680 --> 36:07.910
- YOU'RE OFFICIALLY
MY HERO.

36:08.060 --> 36:10.051
THANK YOU.
- SURE.

36:10.200 --> 36:12.748
- SO THIS IS CHRISTOPHER.

36:12.890 --> 36:14.403
- OH, MY GOD.

36:14.550 --> 36:16.711
- HE'S MY LITTLE ANGEL.

36:16.860 --> 36:18.202
- HI.
- AW!

36:18.340 --> 36:19.682
- WAS THAT FOR ME?
THAT LITTLE SMILE.

36:19.830 --> 36:22.924
- [giggIeS]

36:23.070 --> 36:25.550
DID YOU WANNA HOLD HIM?

36:25.700 --> 36:27.247
- OKAY.
- WANNA GO TO JULIA?

36:27.390 --> 36:29.176
YOU WANNA GO MEET JULIA.

36:29.320 --> 36:32.380
YEAH.

36:35.260 --> 36:38.878
- OH, HI, BUDDY.

36:39.020 --> 36:42.842
[baby snuffling]
- HEY.

36:42.990 --> 36:45.572
HEY, THERE.

36:45.720 --> 36:49.998
OH, YOUR MOMMY'S SO LUCKY.

36:50.130 --> 36:52.951
LOOK AT YOU.

36:53.100 --> 36:56.445
SHE'S SO LUCKY.

36:56.590 --> 36:59.343
HE'S REALLY BEAUTIFUL.

37:01.490 --> 37:04.482
I FORGOT
WHAT THIS WAS LIKE.

37:18.200 --> 37:20.919
- HIYA, HOT STUFF.

37:21.060 --> 37:22.197
- HEY.

37:22.340 --> 37:23.614
- HI.
HOW ARE YOU?

37:23.750 --> 37:25.718
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP
SO LATE?

37:25.860 --> 37:29.921
- JUST, UM...
JUST READING.

37:33.900 --> 37:35.652
- LISTEN, KRISTINA,
I HAVE SOMETHING TO TELL YOU.

37:35.800 --> 37:37.597
- OKAY, I HAVE SOMETHING
TO TELL YOU TOO.

37:37.730 --> 37:39.140
YOU GO FIRST.
- GO AHEAD.

37:39.290 --> 37:40.803
-_ NO.
[giggIeS]

37:40.940 --> 37:44.012
YOU GO.

37:44.150 --> 37:45.879
- [sighs]

37:46.020 --> 37:47.157
- WHAT?

37:47.290 --> 37:51.431
- I GOT FIRED.

37:51.570 --> 37:53.504
- YOU GOT--

37:53.650 --> 37:55.402
- YEAH, I LOST IT ON CORY,

37:55.540 --> 37:58.919
AND HE FIRED ME.

37:59.060 --> 38:01.233
- TODAY?
- TODAY.

38:01.380 --> 38:03.132
I JUST COULDN'T TELL YOU.

38:03.280 --> 38:05.202
- WHO CAR--
YOU KNOW WHAT?

38:05.350 --> 38:06.999
I DON'T LIKE HIM ANYWAY.

38:07.140 --> 38:08.698
AND YOU DON'T
LIKE IT THERE, SO--

38:08.830 --> 38:10.832
- WE'RE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.
WE GOT SOME SAVINGS.

38:10.970 --> 38:12.790
- I KNOW.
- AND I CAN GET A JOB.

38:12.940 --> 38:15.170
- HONEY, ADAM, LISTEN.
- QUICKLY, SO.

38:15.320 --> 38:16.594
- STOP.
- IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

38:16.740 --> 38:17.525
- YOU'VE NEVER LET
THIS FAMILY DOWN, OKAY?

38:17.670 --> 38:18.762
WE'RE GONNA BE FINE.

38:18.910 --> 38:21.049
WE CAN GET
THROUGH THIS TOGETHER.

38:21.190 --> 38:22.293
OKAY?

38:26.510 --> 38:30.219
- WHAT DID
YOU WANNA TELL ME?

38:30.370 --> 38:34.022
- I FOUND AN ORTHODONTIST
THAT CAN MAKE MAX'S RETAINER

38:34.170 --> 38:36.024
FOR $400 INSTEAD OF $700--
- KRISTINA.

38:36.170 --> 38:37.751
- I KNOW.
- NOW IS NOT THE TIME, KRISTINA.

38:37.900 --> 38:39.344
I TOLD YOU I WOULD FIND IT,
AND I'M GONNA FIND IT.

38:39.480 --> 38:40.651
I HAVEN'T LOOKED IN
THE TRASH YET,

38:40.800 --> 38:44.349
AND DAMN IT,
I'M GONNA FIND THAT RETAINER.

38:45.630 --> 38:47.109
- [television]
NO, DON'T TELL ME, LET ME GUESS.

38:47.250 --> 38:50.003
WE ARE A BRIDE
IN SEARCH OF A WEDDING.

38:50.150 --> 38:51.902
- NO.
- NO?

38:52.050 --> 38:54.018
- THERE IS A WEDDING...
- HEY.

38:54.150 --> 38:55.663
- HEY.

38:55.810 --> 38:59.052
- UM...

38:59.190 --> 39:00.942
TRY IT AGAIN.

39:01.090 --> 39:04.093
[television chatter
continues]

39:07.890 --> 39:09.949
- HEY.

39:10.100 --> 39:12.921
[Scott Ainslie's Hard Times
Come Again No More]

39:15.240 --> 39:19.347
- LET US PAUSE
IN LIFE'S PLEASURES

39:19.490 --> 39:22.175
AND COUNT
ITS MANY TEARS

39:22.320 --> 39:26.188
WHY WE ALL SUP SORROW
WITH THE POOR

39:29.670 --> 39:33.117
THERE'S A SONG
THAT WILL LINGER

39:33.260 --> 39:36.013
FOREVER IN OUR EARS

39:36.160 --> 39:38.401
OH, HARD TIMES

39:38.540 --> 39:43.159
COME AGAIN NO MORE

39:43.310 --> 39:46.859
'TIS THE SONG
- HEY.

39:47.000 --> 39:49.139
- HEY.

39:49.280 --> 39:53.865
HOW WAS THE HOSPITAL?
- HARD TIMES, HARD TIMES

39:54.010 --> 39:56.149
- I'M NOT DONE.
- COME AGAIN NO MORE

39:56.290 --> 39:58.838
- I WANT ANOTHER BABY.

39:58.980 --> 40:00.902
- MANY DAYS
HAVE YOU LINGERED

40:01.050 --> 40:04.975
- I WANT TO ADOPT.
- AROUND MY CABIN DOOR

40:05.120 --> 40:08.112
WILL YOU?
- OH, HARD TIMES

40:08.260 --> 40:11.195
COME AGAIN NO MORE

40:13.130 --> 40:16.429
WHILE WE SEEK
MIRTH AND BEAUTY

40:16.580 --> 40:19.401
AND MUSIC BRIGHT
AND GAY

40:19.550 --> 40:22.519
THERE
ARE FRAIL FORMS

40:22.660 --> 40:26.756
FAINTING BY THE DOOR

40:26.900 --> 40:30.654
THOUGH THEIR VOICES
ARE SILENT

40:30.800 --> 40:33.143
THEIR HAUNTING LOOKS
WILL SAY

40:33.290 --> 40:34.564
OH, HAR--

40:36.260 --> 40:38.216
- KRISTINA,
I AM GOING TO KILL HIM.

40:38.360 --> 40:39.668
- I AM SORRY ABOUT THE RETA--
- THAT LITTLE SON OF A BITCH

40:39.810 --> 40:41.698
LOOKED ME IN THE EYE
EARLIER TONIGHT

40:41.850 --> 40:43.363
AND PROMISED ME
THAT HE WOULD USE A CONDOM.

40:43.510 --> 40:44.943
- WHAT ARE YOU TALK--
- APPARENTLY HE WAS LYING TO ME.

40:45.090 --> 40:46.398
- OH.
- BECAUSE HE KNOCKED UP

40:46.540 --> 40:47.609
OUR DAUGHTER.
- OKAY, HEY, WAIT A MIN--

40:47.750 --> 40:48.819
- LOOK WHAT I FOUND
IN THE TRASH.

40:48.960 --> 40:50.404
- NOT FAIR.
YOU KNOW WHAT, HONEY?

40:50.550 --> 40:52.689
HE DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.
- WHY CAN'T ANYTHING GO RIGHT?

40:52.820 --> 40:54.890
WHY CAN'T A SINGLE THING
GO RIGHT AROUND HERE?

40:55.030 --> 40:56.099
WHY DO I HAVE
TO DEAL WITH THIS?

40:56.240 --> 40:57.059
- CALM DOWN, CALM DOWN.

40:57.210 --> 40:58.416
- WHAT?
- EVERYTHING IS OKAY.

40:58.550 --> 40:59.687
- HOW CAN I CALM DOWN?
- IT'S ME.

40:59.830 --> 41:00.728
- OUR 16-YEAR-OLD DAUGHTER

41:00.870 --> 41:02.246
IS PREGNANT!
- IT'S ME.

41:02.390 --> 41:04.108
- WHAT?

41:04.250 --> 41:08.311
- IT'S...ME.

41:08.460 --> 41:12.248
ADAM, I'M PREGNANT.

41:13.850 --> 41:17.251
I AM SO SORRY, I...

41:17.400 --> 41:18.537
- HOW DID THAT HAPPEN?

41:18.680 --> 41:20.056
- EH...

41:20.200 --> 41:21.815
THAT NIGHT AFTER
THE MEXICAN RESTAURANT,

41:21.960 --> 41:24.099
I'M THINKING.
- KRISTINA.

41:24.240 --> 41:26.686
- WE HAD ALL THOSE MARGARITAS.
- I JUST LOST MY JOB.

41:26.820 --> 41:29.061
- HONEY, I KNOW.
- [chuckles] OH, MY GOD.

41:29.210 --> 41:30.780
- I'LL GET A JOB.
I'LL DO SOMETHING.

41:30.930 --> 41:32.795
I JUST--I DON'T--
- COME HERE, COME HERE.

41:32.930 --> 41:34.306
[laughing]
- WHY ARE YOU LAUGHING?

41:34.450 --> 41:35.587
- [laughing]
I DON'T KNOW.

41:35.730 --> 41:37.277
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.
- I KNOW.

41:37.420 --> 41:39.001
YOU'RE NOT--ARE YOU MAD?

41:39.150 --> 41:40.902
- [chuckles]
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I AM.

41:41.050 --> 41:43.837
- YOU'RE--WELL...
I MEAN, I'LL RAISE IT.

41:43.980 --> 41:45.971
- YOU'LL RAISE IT?
- I FOUND MY RETAINER!

41:46.120 --> 41:48.350
OH, MY--DAD, IT WAS
IN GUACAMOLE'S CAGE!

41:48.500 --> 41:50.013
- [laughing]
- I AM AWESOME!

41:50.160 --> 41:52.776
I AM TOTALLY,
TOTALLY AWESOME.

41:52.920 --> 41:55.059
- OKAY, I DON'T KNOW--
- COME HERE.

41:55.200 --> 41:57.339
- YOU'RE NOT MAD?
- I'M NOT MAD, HONEY.

41:57.480 --> 41:59.095
- OKAY.
- I'M FREAKED OUT.

41:59.240 --> 42:00.229
BUT I'M NOT MAD.

42:00.370 --> 42:02.759
- I'M REAL, REAL SCARED,
BUT I'M HAPPY.

42:02.890 --> 42:04.278
YOU HAPPY?
- YEAH.

42:04.410 --> 42:05.684
YEAH.
- OKAY.

42:05.830 --> 42:07.616
- [laughing]
I'M HAPPY.

42:07.760 --> 42:09.204
- OKAY.
WE'RE HAVING A BABY.

42:09.350 --> 42:13.343
- [laughing]
- AROUND MY CABIN DOOR

42:13.490 --> 42:15.936
OH, HARD TIMES

42:16.080 --> 42:19.732
COME AGAIN NO MORE

42:19.880 --> 42:23.566
MM, HARD TIMES

